\fB\-V \fIcolumn1\fR[,column2,... columnN], \fB\-\-view \fIcolumn1\fR[,column2,... columnN]
Specifies a comma-seperated list of table column names which are to be displayed.
All other columns will be ignored.
For a command that produces multiple result tables, the column name list for each table is separated by a slash (\fB/\fR). 
Using this parameter defines a "view" for this and all subsequent invocations of this command; the same column selections will be displayed until the "view" is redefined by the \fB--view\fR option.
To remove a view, specify a null string, i.e. "--view ''", which will cause all defined columns to be displayed.
To see the tables and columns that can be displayed, use the \fB\-\-view-columns\fR option.

Default: None.
